tags.name: Orchard Grove
tags.note: There are actually two cycle entries, one for left turn and one for straight in!

tags.name: John Perrin Place
tags.note: Has Brent Housing Partnership road name (i.e. "council housing")

tags.name: Westglade Court
tags.note: The road name sign doesn't have LB Brent on on it, which generally means it is unadopted.

tags.fixme: Didn't expect name not to be recorded, so didn't make a note of it.
On Bing this looks like a continuation of the higway=residential (private) road.  It also looks to extend further south.

tags.name: Campion Close
tags.note: Lack of Brent branding on signs and general quality of the road makes me think this is unadopted.
tags.note:lit: There is a light at the entrance and by the footpath, but it is not clear that these are lighting the road.

tags.fixme: Does this actually join the main road? Would destination be better than private (roughly, is it used by univited visitors)?
tags.note: OS codes this as not a highway (no casing) and I never noticed it on the ground.

tags.name: Preston Hill
tags.source: Survey of 2013-09-20 (tag accidentially missed from comment in changeset 17940010)

tags.note: Sign says: Brent Council, Private Road, No Parking. Treating as destination because ungated, has sidewalk, and serving multiple entrances.

tags.name: Woodgrange Avenue
tags.note: The southern sidewalk narrows down to about a foot in this section, eventually being blocked by a reasonable overhang of bushes, so I think it is reasonable to say there is none for about 14m east from the junction kerb.

tags.name: Sandy Lane
tags.note: Naming of bus stop suggests whole length should be Sandy Lane.  Lit to adopted footpath standard.

tags.name: Sandy Lane
tags.note: Signed with standard Brent street name at E.  Lit.  OS says private but looks like adopted for vehicles.

tags.name: John Perrin Place
tags.note: Although this has a private, parking restricted sign, it has an adopted street type name board. I'm assuming the surface change on Bing represents the switch to private.

tags.note:access: This is explicitly signed as being private to the West of PROW 17 (yet to be mapped), but is clearly private all the way except for foot.
